    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-16T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-16T02:00:00-05:00" n="405"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890G.5123/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Farrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-16T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 16, 1942—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>119. Basra agents of Isthmian Steamship Lines insist on accounting for Iraqi
                    income tax on earnings of vessels operated by Maritime Commission. Before I
                    approach Iraqi Government please instruct whether <pb facs="0359" n="347"
                        xml:id="pg_347"/> vessels so operated are considered by our Government as
                    liable to income tax here on freight and passenger earnings ex Iraq.</p>
                <p>Isthmian Steamship Company, New York, has instructed its Basra agents to pay only
                    under protest and Maritime Commission representative Basra desires Legation to
                    intervene with Iraqi revenue authorities.</p>
                <p>Foregoing repeated by air mail to Tehran as similar situation is understood to
                    exist.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Farrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
